      <h2 class="m-0 text-[30px] font-extrabold tracking-[-0.02em] text-ink">Your data stays yours</h2>
    </div>
    <div>
      <p class="m-0 text-[18px] leading-[1.65] text-pretty text-[#5e574f]">
        Trackie runs entirely over a secure connection, for New Zealand only. Sign
        in is just your email and a one-time code - no password to leak. If you
        choose to connect a bank later, that connection is <strong class="font-bold text-ink"
          >read-only</strong
        >: Trackie can see your transactions to help you budget, but it can never
        move your money, and you can switch it off any time. Prefer to keep banks
        out of it? Importing a statement by hand is a fully supported way to use
        Trackie, start to finish.
      </p>
